<div class="snippet">
  <style>{{{style}}}</style>
  <script>{{{script}}}</script>
  <script>$(Snippet.start)</script>
  <img class="icon" src="{{{icon}}}" />

  <div class="snippet-content">
    <div id="snippet-pg-1">
      <p>Hey you, maker! Want to redesign this page? <a id="snippet-begin" href="#">Click here</a> to change the background.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="snippet-pg-2" style="display: none">
      <p>This is the CSS required to change the background of the page.</p>
      <code>body { background: <span id="snippet-css-container"><span class="arrow-box">Try pressing backspace a few times.</span><input type="text" id="snippet-css" autocomplete="off" /></span> }</code>
      <p id="snippet-end">Not too shabby! Curious to learn more about what&rsquo;s under the hood of a webpage? Visit <a href="http://welcome.webmaker.org">Webmaker.org</a> to create and remix the web.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="body-frame">
  <div class="arrow-box"><code>background</code> is a style property that sets the background of an element on a web page.</div>
</div>
